"1410":"1410","1399":"1399","1475":"1475","1420":"1420","1353":"1353","1408":"1408","Rock Hall, Dumfries-shire, Scotland":"Rock Hall, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Dumfries, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, (1st Feudal Lord of Lagg)":"Dumfries, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Estate of Rock Hall, Collin, Dumfries-shire, Scotland":"Collin, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Old Dunscore Cemetery Dunscore, Dumfries and Galloway, Scotland":"Dunscore, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"McAlpine","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and Irish (Mayo and Tyrone): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Ailpein</b> (Scottish) or <b>Mac Ailpín</b> (Irish) ‘son of <i>Ailpean</i>’, a personal name derived from <i>alp</i> ‘lump’. The personal name was borne by Pictish kings, one of whom, Kenneth, son of Ailpín or Ailpean, became the ruler of the united Picts and Scots."],"variants":[{"name":"McAlpin","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   McAlpine  ."]},{"name":"McNab","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: Anglicized form of Scottish Gaelic <b>Mac an Aba(dh)</b> ‘son of the abbot’.","History: This is the name of a Scottish clan claiming descent from Abraruadh, Abbot of Glen Dochart, Perths, in the 9th century. In Scotland many monasteries were controlled by hereditary lay abbots. Abraruadh is said to have been a younger son of King Kenneth Mac Alpine (Coinneach mac Ailpein; see   McAlpine  ). According to another tradition, the clan founder was a lay abbot of Glen Dochart at the time of King David I (1124–53). Malcolm de Glendochart is recorded in the Ragman Rolls (1296) and was no doubt a member of this clan."]},{"name":"McCoppin","meanings":["Scottish or northern Irish: probably an altered form of <b>McCappin</b>, which is a variant of   McAlpine  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary McAlpine of Finnick was born in 1280, in Rock Hall, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, her father, Malice McAlpine, was -128 and her mother, Margaret DeSomerville, was -130. She had at least 4 sons with Lord Malcolm MacGregor. She died on 17 June 1363, in Collin, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 83, and was buried in Dunscore, Dumfriesshire, Scotland."},"et":{"1280–17 June 1363":"1280–17. juuni 1363","1280–1363":"1280–1363","1297–1374":"1297–1374","1353–1425":"1353–1425","1399–1457":"1399–1457","1420–1473":"1420–1473","1424–1473":"1424–1473","1408–1475":"1408–1475","1410–1470":"1410–1470","17 June 1363":"17. juuni 1363","1473":"1473","1374":"1374","1297":"1297","1363":"1363","1470":"1470","1280":"1280","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1457":"1457","1410":"1410","1399":"1399","1475":"1475","1420":"1420","1353":"1353","1408":"1408","Rock Hall, Dumfries-shire, Scotland":"Rock Hall, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Dumfries, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, (1st Feudal Lord of Lagg)":"Dumfries, Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Estate of Rock Hall, Collin, Dumfries-shire, Scotland":"Collin, Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Old Dunscore Cemetery Dunscore, Dumfries and Galloway, Scotland":"Dunscore, Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1280–17 June 1363":"1280–17. kesäkuuta 1363","1280–1363":"1280–1363","1297–1374":"1297–1374","1353–1425":"1353–1425","1399–1457":"1399–1457","1420–1473":"1420–1473","1424–1473":"1424–1473","1408–1475":"1408–1475","1410–1470":"1410–1470","17 June 1363":"17. kesäkuuta 1363","1473":"1473","1374":"1374","1297":"1297","1363":"1363","1470":"1470","1280":"1280","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1457":"1457","1410":"1410","1399":"1399","1475":"1475","1420":"1420","1353":"1353","1408":"1408","Rock Hall, Dumfries-shire, Scotland":"Rock Hall, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Dumfries, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, (1st Feudal Lo